# NIX SHELL
Nixpkgs: nixpkgs.nix
Source: https://github.com/NixOS/nix
Description: Run a shell in which the specified packages are available.
Version: nix --version

## Commands

### Basics
- nix shell nixpkgs#htop: Open a shell with htop available.
- nix shell nixpkgs#python3 nixpkgs#numpy: Shell with multiple packages.

### Essentials
- nix shell .#my-app: Open a shell defined in the local flake.
- nix shell --ignore-environment nixpkgs#git: Open a pure shell (no inherited PATH).

### Intermediaries
- nix shell nixpkgs#go --command go version: Run a specific command without entering interactive mode.

### Advanceds
- nix shell github:edolstra/dwarffs: Open a shell from a remote flake URL.

### Uncommons
- nix shell nixpkgs#gcc --impure: Allow access to environment variables like CC.

## Tips
- Packages are only available in the current session and not installed globally.

## Disclaimers
- Does not provide a development environment (use nix develop for that).

## Alternatives
- nix develop: Better for project development (sets up environment variables).

